\id MRK - Plain English Version 
\h Mark 
\toc3 Mark 
\toc2 Mark 
\toc1 The Good News According to Mark 
\mt1 Mark wrote this good news about Jesus  
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk Mark\bk*)  
\imt1 About this book  
\ip The Holy Bible has 4 books about the things that Jesus did, and the messages he told to people when he was here on the earth, about 2,000 years ago. Those books are in the 2nd part of the Holy Bible, called the \em New Testament\em*. The men that wrote them were Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John. They wrote their books after Jesus went back to heaven. Most of the things in their books happened in the country we now call Israel.  
\ip This book has everything that Mark wrote about Jesus. It is important for us today because it tells us about the good things that Jesus did, and the messages that he brought to us from God.  
\ip Mark was a young man when Jesus was here on the earth. He probably knew Jesus and Jesus’s special workers very well. Some of the things he wrote about are things he probably saw happen, and the rest he probably heard about from Peter and other people that saw them happen. Mark wrote this book about 20 or 30 years after those things happened.  
\ip Mark was sometimes called John Mark. His mother had a house in Jerusalem city, and after Jesus went back to heaven, his followers sometimes met together in Mark’s mother’s house (see Acts 12:12). Some time later, Paul and Barnabas went to lots of different places to tell people about Jesus, and they took Mark with them to help them (see Acts 13:5; 15:36-39; 2 Timothy 4:11). He was a friend of Peter and a cousin of Barnabas (see Colossians 4:10).  
\cl Chapter  
\c 1  
\s1 John baptised people  
\p
\v 1 \w This|strong="G3588"\w* story \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w good|strong="G3588"\w* \w news|strong="G2098"\w*. \w It|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w all|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G2424"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w God|strong="G3588"\w*’s son. \w The|strong="G3588"\w* story starts like \w this|strong="G3588"\w*.   
\p
\v 2-3 A long time before Jesus was born, God told a man called Isaiah to write in God’s book about something God was going to do for Jesus. And it happened the way Isaiah wrote. He wrote this,  
\q1 “God will send a man to get everything ready for him.  
\q1 That man will talk about him and make a way for people to listen to him.  
\q1 That man will be out in the bush, and he will call out to people, and he will say, ‘You mob get ready.  
\q1 God is coming to this country, so you have to get ready for him.  
\q1 It is like when a big boss comes, and you have to make a good road for him.’”\x * \xo 1:2-3 \xt Isaiah 40:3; Malachi 3:1\x*   
\m
\v 4-6 Isaiah was talking about a man called John. God sent him to get things ready for Jesus, so he started to tell people God’s message. He lived out in the bush and wore rough clothes made out of camel’s hair, and a leather belt. He ate grasshoppers and bush honey.\x * \xo 1:4-6 \xt 2 Kings 1:8\x*  
\p John talked to people out there in the bush. He said, “You mob have to be really sorry for the wrong way you are living. You have to turn right around and live God’s way.” He also told them, “If you do that, I will baptise you. That means, I will take you through a special washing ceremony. And God will not do payback for the bad things you did.”  
\p A lot of people went out into the bush to listen to John. They came from the city called Jerusalem and from other towns in that country called Judea. Some people told John that they were sorry for the wrong things they did, so he baptised them in the Jordan River.   
\p
